The paper deals with the problem of estimating parameters of mixtures of spherical Gaussians, which is a common problem in machine learning and statistics. The paper proposes a moment-based estimator that is computationally efficient and statistically consistent. The paper also makes connections to estimation problems related to independent component analysis. Based on these factors, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves information theory (IT) and numerical analysis (NA) techniques, which make cs.IT and cs.NA likely sub-categories. The paper also involves some signal processing (SI) techniques related to independent component analysis. Finally, the paper involves some artificial intelligence (AI) techniques related to unsupervised learning.
